flowRoot.flowPara: Desktop: Headers for Folders and Conversations are merged. If selection mode is enabled for either, the action bar appears under the list that has entered selection mode. If we shrink the window down smaller than possible to show three panes, it enters single-pane mode as above, there is no "double pane" intermediate.

Composers also gain an action bar at the bottom of the window and action buttons are moved there. An overflow menu is used for switching between rich/plaintext, adding additional fields (CC, BCC, etc) and... other things?. The formatting toolbar drop down remains effectively as a overflow menu for formatting items.
Conversation list: Same view as is desktop mode, but with an Back button to return to Folders. Search and secondary menu not included initially.
When selection mode is enabled, an action bar apears to allow conversations to be updated:
Folders: Same view as in desktop mode. Primary
menu containing app menu and folder-specific options
When selection mode is enabled, an action bar apears to allow folders to mark all as read, get deleted, etc
Conversation: Same view as in desktop mode. Back
returns to conversation list. Find button invokes in-conversation find. Secondary menu hasview options.
Here, an action bar is displayed by default.
These action bars need to be fleshed out more:
Composer: Header bar title is updated to reflect subject when entered. Secondary menu contains composer options such as rich/plain mode.
Here, an action bar is displayed by default.
Composer: Alternative with subject in the header bar and replies default to drop-downs instead of text fields.
